From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000002 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: therockbot <therockbot@amd.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 00:00:01 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] rpp: guard test-suite OpenCV-only compare helper

The image test suite is designed to build without OpenCV: every OpenCV
include and call site is wrapped in
`#if defined(RPP_TEST_SUITE_HAVE_OPENCV) && RPP_TEST_SUITE_HAVE_OPENCV`,
and the call sites fall back to a warning when OpenCV is absent (see
Tensor_image_host.cpp around the write_image_batch_opencv call).

The helper `compare_output_single_image()` was added to
rpp_test_suite_image.h without that guard. Because it is an `inline`
function taking `const vector<cv::Mat>&`, it is fully parsed whenever the
header is included, even when it is never called. On a test runner
without OpenCV (TheRock builds the suite with
-DRPP_TEST_SUITE_HAVE_OPENCV=0) this breaks the build:

  rpp_test_suite_image.h:2472:54: error: use of undeclared identifier 'cv'
   inline void compare_output_single_image(const vector<cv::Mat>& ...

Wrap the helper in the same RPP_TEST_SUITE_HAVE_OPENCV guard as the rest
of the OpenCV-dependent code. It is only ever invoked from already-guarded
sections, so no functionality is lost when OpenCV is available.

Upstream tracking: https://github.com/ROCm/rocm-libraries/pull/8295
Once that merges and TheRock's rocm-libraries submodule is bumped past it,
this patch can be dropped.

Signed-off-by: therockbot <therockbot@amd.com>
---
 projects/rpp/utilities/test_suite/rpp_test_suite_image.h | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/projects/rpp/utilities/test_suite/rpp_test_suite_image.h b/projects/rpp/utilities/test_suite/rpp_test_suite_image.h
--- a/projects/rpp/utilities/test_suite/rpp_test_suite_image.h
+++ b/projects/rpp/utilities/test_suite/rpp_test_suite_image.h
@@ -2467,6 +2467,7 @@ void fill_perm_values(Rpp32u *permTensor, bool qaMode, int permOrder)
         permTensor[i] = mapping[permOrder][i];
 }
 
+#if defined(RPP_TEST_SUITE_HAVE_OPENCV) && RPP_TEST_SUITE_HAVE_OPENCV
 // Compare output for single image processing mode
 // Only supports: BRIGHTNESS (0), BLEND (2), FLIP (20), RESIZE (21), CROP (37), BOX_FILTER (49), MEDIAN_FILTER (51), GAUSSIAN_FILTER (54)
 inline void compare_output_single_image(const vector<cv::Mat>& outputVec, const vector<RpptDesc>& srcDescPtr, const vector<RpptDesc>& dstDescPtr, string funcName, RpptImagePatch *dstImgSizes, int noOfImages, string interpolationTypeName, string noiseTypeName, int additionalParam, int testCase, string dst, string scriptPath)
@@ -2692,3 +2693,4 @@ inline void compare_output_single_image(const vector<cv::Mat>& outputVec, const
         qaResults.close();
     }
 }
+#endif /* RPP_TEST_SUITE_HAVE_OPENCV */
